Officers responded to the Tolbos Street shooting on Monday morning where a man had been shot several times. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating a case of murder after a man was gunned down in Bonteheuwel.Officers responded to the Tolbos Street shooting in the early hours of Monday morning.The victim had been shot several times.The police s Noloyiso Rwexana said, The victim sustained gunshot wounds to his body and died due to his injuries. No one has been arrested at this stage. Six people have been shot and killed during gang-related clashes in Bonteheuwel over the past few months.Angry residents took to the streets earlier in December after 18-year-old Modderdam High School pupil Dylan Pelton was gunned down.